# Deities & Demigods — Mythworld Engine v2.12.1

## Project Overview
AI-driven mythological RPG powered by DDG 1980 compendium. 3-act structure, Gaiman-style narration, permadeath, prophecy, shard system, companion affinity, divine combat. Dual-engine DM: Gemini (narrative) + LM Studio (mechanics).

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui, custom medieval dark theme
- AI DM: Gemini 2.5 Flash via /api/gemini proxy (server-side, 3-tier fallback)
- AI Mechanics: LM Studio via /api/lmstudio proxy (local LLM, falls back to Gemini)
- AI Actions: Groq API for 6 player action options per turn
- TTS: Browser Web Speech API (primary) + Edge TTS /api/tts (fallback)
- Comic Panels: /api/generate-image, Larry Elmore style, lazy-loaded
- Database: SQLite via Prisma (170+ DDG entities, query-only)
- State: React state in useGameEngine.ts + localStorage save/load
- Deployment: Vercel serverless | PWA manifest

## Architecture
- src/hooks/useGameEngine.ts (~4100 lines) — THE monolith. ALL game logic. Changes require extreme care.
- src/app/page.tsx (~3900 lines) — All UI rendering in one file
- src/lib/gameConstants.ts — GEMINI_MODEL, SHARD_NAMES, INJURY_TABLE, ITEM_TEMPLATES, ANTAGONIST_CLUES
- src/lib/gameTypes.ts — All TS interfaces (GameState, PlayerCharacter, DMResponse)
- src/lib/characterData.ts — DDG 1980 entities (heroes, demigods, gods, monsters)
- src/lib/krynnCharacters.ts — Dragonlance entities
- src/lib/prophecyData.ts — 9 prophecies (d9 roll, Gaiman-style riddles)
- src/lib/antagonistPool.ts — Boss pool (Greater Gods HP>=300 + Super Monsters)
- src/lib/fallbackEntities.ts — Fallback data when API fails
- src/lib/comicPanelGenerator.ts — Splits narration into 2-4 comic panels
- src/components/game/ComicPanel.tsx — Comic panel grid UI
- src/app/api/gemini/route.ts — Server-side Gemini proxy (3-tier: Flash → Gemma 4 → Flash-Lite)
- src/app/api/lmstudio/route.ts — LM Studio local LLM proxy
- src/app/api/generate-image/route.ts — Image generation for comic panels
- src/app/api/tts/route.ts — Edge TTS endpoint
- src/app/api/game-entities/route.ts — Entity database query

## Critical Constraints
- Gemini calls MUST go through /api/gemini proxy. NEVER call generativelanguage.googleapis.com directly from client. No exposed API keys.
- /api/gemini handles retries + 3-tier fallback server-side. Client should NOT retry Gemini calls.
- LM Studio fallback to Gemini must work WITHOUT any client-side API key check.
- Zero TS errors. No any types.
- JSON parse failure: use getNarrationPreservationFallback() NEVER getTemplateFallback().
- maxOutputTokens: 6144 regular turns, 20000 opening turns.
- Mobile-first: 48px touch targets, safe-area-inset, viewport-fit cover, no pinch-zoom.

## Game Systems
- ACTS: I (intro, shadow antagonist, 10-100 turns) → II (full party, clues, 20-60 turns) → III (boss fight, 3 phases)
- PC STRUCTURE: 1 Main PC (shard carrier) + 1 Companion (affinity -100 to +100) + 3 RNG Heroes + 3 RNG Demigods
- SHARD: Central plot device, chose main PC, whispers visions, senses antagonist, pantheon affinity, 2 summoning charges
- PROPHECY: Bound to shard, d9 roll for riddle, states dormant→awakening→manifesting→fulfilled, transfers on PC death
- ANTAGONIST: Random Greater God (HP>=300) or Super Monster, hidden until Act III, clues revealed gradually
- COMBAT: d20 vs DC, damage/injury via JSON state, INJURY_TABLE for effects
- SUCCESS RATE: 50% base + 2/living PC + 3-8/prophecy state + 3/allied god, each factor capped at +5%
- PERMADEATH: Real death, shard summons replacement, prophecy transfers
- COMPANION AFFINITY: -100 to +100, moods: devoted/loyal/concerned/conflicted/hostile
- COMIC PANELS: 2-4 panels per turn, Larry Elmore style, toggle on/off, lazy-loaded
- SAVE/LOAD: localStorage with safeLocalStorageGetItem/SetItem (no TDZ), quota handling

## TTS Dual Engine
- Browser (default): window.speechSynthesis, zero server dependency
- Neural (fallback): /api/tts, Edge TTS
- localStorage keys: ddg_tts_engine, ddg_browser_voice

## Code Style
- Functional components + hooks only. Tailwind medieval dark palette.
- console.error for errors, console.log for success tracking, console.warn for warnings.
- Mobile-first responsive: sm: breakpoint for tablet, md: for desktop.

